symposium.model

Class TimeConstraint

  • java.lang.Object
    • symposium.model.Constraint
      • symposium.model.TimeConstraint
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    NewPanelistConstraint

    abstract class TimeConstraint
extends Constraint
    The class TimeConstraint is an abstract which inherits from Constraints, @see Constraint for documentation. The class is the parent class, which represents any constraints that tests the panel or panelist on a specific time. For example, the New Panelist Constraint is a time constraint, such as we test whether the panelist on the first day is new or not. Testing the first day means we are testing a specific time. Constraint is violated when the checked time doesn't satisfy the wanted time
